profile_positions.description:
Consultant with the Climate and Environment Division:
- Analysis of the Nationally Determined Contributions on policy and institutional coherence for climate action in the agriculture sectors of developing countries;
- Coordination of FAO's involvement in the UNFCCC and other high-level meetings, including by preparing official submissions, reports and speeches; 
- Liaise with relevant FAO Divisions, other UN agencies, non-governmental organisations, research institutes, and the private sector;
- Preparation of project proposal on policy coherence between climate and agricultural sectors in developing countries;
- Preparation of project proposal on downward accountability and civil society engagement in international climate reporting and review mechanisms in developing countries.
